def: A modified form of dentine, which is permeated by bloodcapillaries; vascular dentine.
To bear fruit. "Causeth the earth to fructify." Beveridge.
A French partisan soldier, or one belonging to a corps ofdetached light troops engaged in forays, skirmishes, scouting, etc.
An order of birds which formerly included all the waders. Bylater writers it is usually restricted to the sandpipers, plovers,and allied forms; -- called also Grallatores.
Having some of the forms, such as drapery or the like, toosharply defined. "An edgy style of sculpture." Hazlitt.
Speech or discourse; a phrase; a form or mode of expression. "Stumbling locutions." G. Eliot.I hate these figures in locution, These about phrases forced byceremony. Marston.
A palace and mausoleum of the kinds of Spain, being a vast andwonderful structure about twenty-five miles northwest of Madrid.
To stop (a leak in a ship at sea) by drawing under its bottom athrummed sail, so that the pressure of the water may force it intothe crack. Totten.
Having a sting; covered with prickles; sharp like a prickle.
Capable of being heard; loud enough to be heard; actuallyheard; as, an audible voice or whisper.
